category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther
name: Swiss Naturalistas

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther
name: Swiss Naturalistas

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther
name: Swiss Naturalistas

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.
name: Geneva Black Hair
organizer.name: Angie Brice Hessbruegge

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther
name: Swiss Naturalistas

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.
name: Geneva Black Hair

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther
name: Swiss Naturalistas

If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.
name: Geneva Black Hair

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.
name: Geneva Black Hair

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

description:
Whether you are new to the area and/or looking to take care of you or your child's hair, this bi-lingual (English/French) group for women (and men) will meetup to discuss and learn about: - Black/Afro hair 101- learn about the history, textures, hair types (kinky, nappy, curly, biracial, mixed, etc.) - How to maintain (wash, condition, styling) - Hair care options - developing your own routine (braiding, twisting, extensions, etc.) - Hair care for children (do's and don'ts) - Hair care for adults (dealing with hair loss, promoting hair growth, etc.) - Chemical free products (damage control) - Transitioning from relaxed to natural Meetups will vary in form: workshops, get togethers, support groups, events, etc. This group is open to all who want to learn about black hair. Suggestions for other hair care topics are welcome.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Que vous soyez nouvelle dans le coin et/ou que vous cherchiez une manière de prendre soin de vos et/ou des cheveux de vos enfants, ce groupe bilingue (français/anglais) pour femmes (et hommes) ce groupe se rencontrera pour discuter et pour apprendre: -Cheveux afro L'histoire, les textures, les types de cheveux (crépus, naturels, bouclés, métissés...) - Comment les entretenir (laver, hydrater, coiffer) - Les différentes options pour s'occuper de ses cheveux - Se créer sa propre routine (faire des tresses, des twist, les extensions etc...) -S'occuper des cheveux de vos enfants (à faire et à ne pas faire)- S'occuper des cheveux d'adultes (comment gérer la chute de cheveux, comment optimiser la repousse...) - Les produits sans ajouts chimiques (contrôler les dommages).Les rencontres "transition du cheveu défrisé au cheveu naturel" se distingueront ainsi: des workshops, des rencontres, des groupes de soutien, des événements etc...Ce groupe est ouvert à tous ceux voulant en savoir plus sur le cheveu afro.Les suggestions pour d'autres sujets à traiter sont les bienvenus.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther

description:
Inside each of us is a unique spark, an inner glow from which our true, undeniable beauty originates. This group is for every woman to tend to that inner glow. It's all about feeling great and looking great! ABOUT THIS GROUP

Your social calendar just got a lot more interesting! When you join Free Fitness and Beauty Events In Pretty Woman meet up group, you'll get the latest beauty and fitness related parties, socials, in store events, launches, workshops all happening in Zürich.

If you don't know anyone else at the event because your friends are stuck at work / are too lame to go out / hate anything that doesn't involve drinking / or you're new in town?

That's where being a member of this meet up comes in handy! Because now you'll have a group of people who share your passion for all things beauty / fashion / fitness attending the events and your great meet up host to facilitate the introductions and conversations. You'll also get exposed to new beauty brands that you may become a lifelong fan of!

We will be doing #brunch #lunch #dinner #daytrips #healthyactivities #sharing and learning tools in beauty&fitness #share our experience#beautysessions

#learn tips to increase vitality and weight loss #meet people in Zürich who are interested in beautiful, healthy, happy living!

Everyone who is interested in beauty, health, wellness and fashion should join our group.

PLEASE NOTE: <br>While we plan to organize many of our own exclusive events for members (the more members the more pull we have - so invite your friends!). I hope you'll see how awesome our group is and the immense value we have to offer.

category.name: fashion/beauty
description:
Calling all Naturalistas living in Switzerland! Do you or your loved ones have naturally curly hair, dreadlocks, twists, or any mix of coils & kinks? Do you often find yourself wishing for straight, easy to manage hair? Or maybe you're thinking of transitioning from chemically treated hair to your natural hair texture? If you answered yes, then this group is for you!

This group is for anyone living in Switzerland who is interested in managing their natural kinks, curls, coils, locs & twists beautifully and affordably. I moved to Switzerland from California in 2011, and I've found it difficult to find products and professional stylists who deal with natural curly-textured hair. I decided to form this group as a way to socialize and meet with folks living in Switzerland who may have a similar problem and have had to be "creative" to manage their natural hair. My two daughters are biracial and managing their wild curls with what's available here has been an adventure:)! So, if you're not curly-haired yourself but have children who are, then please join also--you're welcome!

Although I'm based in Zurich, this group is open to all Naturalistas in Switzerland. If you're based in another city then please join and consider being an admin of the group to manage events in your city.

I'll arrange events every 3 months and we'll cover hair management topics. We can review products & styles, share ideas and support one another. We'll also have 'CurlsNightOut', our regular, fun, networking events . Join us and we look forward to meeting you at an event soon!
~Esther
name: Swiss Naturalistas
